376529: Sudden Spoiling.text_posted:
@I_Cheesus: Sudden Spoiling takes away the abilities of the creature, but not the abilities of non-creatures that are buffing those creatures.  However, any abilities granted to the creature ("enchanted/equipped creature has...", usually keyword abilities or activated abilities) will be lost.  So if you have, say, a [autocard]Sword of Feast and Famine[/autocard], the creature will lose protection from green and black (unless the sword is removed and re-attached) but still get +2/+2 and the sword's combat damage trigger will still function.  [autocard]Rancor[/autocard] would still give +2/+0 but trample would be removed.  [autocard]Unflinching Courage[/autocard] will stop giving lifelink but [autocard]Armadillo Cloak[/autocard] will still have its lifelink-esque trigger.  Unblockablility or "can't be blocked" (such as from [autocard]Whispersilk Cloak[/autocard]) will never be affected.

These rules also count for permanents not directly attached to the creature; Sudden Spoiling will nullify an [autocard]Akroma's Memorial[/autocard], but not a [autocard]Coat of Arms[/autocard].

+1/+1 and -1/-1 counters will always continue to function under pretty much any circumstance, Sudden Spoiling included.

